annotationA: Nicotinamide amidase, isoform A; Nicotinamidase activity; calcium ion binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: response to oxidative stress; determination of adult lifespan; negative regulation of neuron apoptotic process; metabolic process
annotationB: Nicotinamide mononucleotide adenylyltransferase (Nmnat) is an essential enzyme in the NAD salvage pathway, catalyzing the last step of NAD synthesis. Nmnat is also a neuronal maintenance factor that protects neurons from excitotoxicity, environmental stress and protein misfolding induced degeneration
